Class CompassPlot

java.lang.Object
  org.jfree.chart.block.AbstractContentBlock
      org.jfree.chart.plot.Plot
          org.jfree.chart.plot.CompassPlot
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.EventListener, Block, ContentBlock, AxisChangeListener, LegendItemSource, DatasetChangeListener, org.jfree.ui.Drawable, org.jfree.util.PublicCloneable
public class CompassPlot
extends Plot
implements Block, java.lang.Cloneable, java.io.Serializable

A specialised plot that draws a compass to indicate a direction based on the value from a ValueDataset.

Author:
Bryan Scott

setSeriesNeedle

public void setSeriesNeedle(int index,
                            int type)
Sets the needle for a series. The needle type is one of the following:
  • 0 = ArrowNeedle;
  • 1 = LineNeedle;
  • 2 = LongNeedle;
  • 3 = PinNeedle;
  • 4 = PlumNeedle;
  • 5 = PointerNeedle;
  • 6 = ShipNeedle;
  • 7 = WindNeedle;
  • 8 = ArrowNeedle;
  • 9 = MiddlePinNeedle;

Parameters:
index - the series index.
type - the needle type.
